All of Europe is in the grip of inflation, and Ireland is no different. But Ireland already had some of the highest prices in Europe across a range of products and services including energy, food, broadband and mortgages. [ Analysis: Why is the Republic of Ireland such an expensive country? ] What’s behind our high prices - and could our own consumer culture have anything to do with it? Conor Pope talks to consumer expert Dargh Cassidy of bonkers.ie.